The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Preferential issue from Escorts

 New Delhi, Feb. 17 (PTI): Escorts Ltd today announced its financial restructuring strategy, under which it will offer preferential shares to non-resident investors and increase its authorised share capital.

 The company will restructure its authorised share capital by consolidating existing unclassified shares of Rs 333 crore and increase it by creating further unclassified shares up to an amount of Rs 440 crore, Escorts has informed the Bombay Stock Exchange.

 Besides, the company will also issue its securities on a preferential basis, up to an extent of Rs 777.76 crore, in favour of overseas investors by way of cumulative redeemable preference shares.

 The financial restructuring programme of the company is subject to regulatory approvals and permissions. The Escorts board has already given its nod to the proposal.




